## 17. Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: Core Merge Function (Weeks 1–3)

- [ ] Implement `_bt_merge_pages()` in `nbtpage.c`
  - Build merged page in temp buffer (`PGAlignedBlock`, same as `_bt_split()`)
  - Reuse `_bt_pgaddtup()` for tuple insertion
  - Always L→R: high key from R, parent pivot identical to `_bt_mark_page_halfdead()`
  - Lock parent via `_bt_lock_subtree_parent()` (nbtpage.c:2817)
  - Update parent pivot: use `BTreeTupleSetDownLink()` +
    `PageIndexTupleDelete()` (same primitives as `_bt_mark_page_halfdead()`)
  - Replace destination page content with merged temp page
  - Mark source as `BTP_HALF_DEAD`
  - Transfer predicate locks via `PredicateLockPageCombine()`
  - WAL log `XLOG_BTREE_MERGE` — 3 blocks
  - Call `_bt_unlink_halfdead_page()` (nbtpage.c:2316) to complete Phase 2
- [ ] Implement `btree_xlog_merge()` in `nbtxlog.c`
  - Replay destination: `_bt_pageinit()` + `_bt_restore_page()` (same as
    `btree_xlog_split()` at nbtxlog.c:275)
  - Replay source: `_bt_pageinit()` + set `BTP_HALF_DEAD` + restore
    truncated high key (same as `btree_xlog_mark_page_halfdead()`)
  - Replay parent: `BTreeTupleSetDownLink()` + `PageIndexTupleDelete()`
- [ ] Add `xl_btree_merge` struct + `XLOG_BTREE_MERGE` to `nbtxlog.h`
- [ ] Add `XLOG_BTREE_MERGE` case to `btree_desc()` in `nbtdesc.c`
- [ ] Basic regression test + amcheck verification
- [ ] **Milestone:** Can manually trigger a merge on two pages, passes amcheck

### Phase 2: Command & Candidate Detection (Weeks 4–6)

- [ ] Implement `_bt_try_merge()` — top-level merge orchestrator
  - Search stack via `_bt_search()` (nbtsearch.c:99)
  - L/R cleanup locks via `LockBufferForCleanup()` (bufmgr.c:6701)
  - All validation checks (see Section 13)
  - Same-parent check via `_bt_lock_subtree_parent()` cross-check
  - Calls `_bt_merge_pages()` for the critical section
- [ ] Add `_bt_is_merge_candidate()` and `_bt_can_merge_into()`
- [ ] Add GUC parameters in `guc_tables.c`
- [ ] Implement the new command's scan loop: iterate leaf pages,
  identify candidates, pick direction, invoke `_bt_try_merge()`
- [ ] **Milestone:** New command automatically merges bloated pages

### Phase 3: Concurrency & Safety (Weeks 7–9)

- [ ] Write isolation tests (forward scan, backward scan during merge)
- [ ] Write crash recovery TAP tests
- [ ] Test with concurrent inserts into merge range
- [ ] Test with concurrent `_bt_pagedel()` on adjacent pages
- [ ] Handle edge cases (posting lists, LP_DEAD, incomplete splits)
- [ ] Test L→R merge with amcheck verification
- [ ] **Milestone:** All concurrency and crash tests pass

### Phase 4: Performance & Polish (Weeks 10–12)

- [ ] Benchmark with pgbench (bloat reduction, lock duration, query impact)
- [ ] Test various GUC threshold combinations
- [ ] Optimize: skip pages already checked, avoid redundant search stacks
- [ ] Documentation (sgml docs, code comments following PostgreSQL style)
- [ ] Prepare patch for pgsql-hackers review
- [ ] **Milestone:** Patch ready for community review

